annotationA: Protein-arginine N-methyltransferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: protein methylation; Belongs to the class I-like SAM-binding methyltransferase superfamily. Protein arginine N- methyltransferase family
annotationB: Protein arginine N-methyltransferase 7; Essential arginine methyltransferase that can both catalyze the formation of omega-N monomethylarginine (MMA) and symmetrical dimethylarginine (sDMA). Specifically mediates the symmetrical dimethylation of arginine residues in the small nuclear ribonucleoproteins SmD1 and SmD3
